place.name: BOTHAMSALL
place.gazetteerText: BOTHAMSALL, a parish in East Retford district, Notts; on the river Medan, 5½ miles NNE of Ollerton, and 6 WNW of Tuxford r. station. Post Town, Walesby, under Newark. Acres, 1,630. Real property, £2,275. Pop., 296. Houses, 57. The property is all in one estate. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £52. Patron, the Duke of Newcastle. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
